<item>
            <title>[ELY-641] Unsafe Elytron role/permission mapping</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ELY-641</link>
                <project id="12315320" key="ELY">WildFly Elytron</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Default Elytron configuration assigns role &quot;All&quot; to every user during authentication. If a deployed application uses such the role name for a resource protection, then every authenticated user can access the protected resource. So the security is bypassed then.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is caused by workaround used for mapping &quot;LoginPermission&quot; to all users. It maps role &quot;All&quot; to the users first and then maps &quot;LoginPermission&quot; to this role.&lt;/p&gt;

